KSEF_BATCH_AUTO_CREATE_SUPPLIERS_SETTING=Auto-create suppliers during batch import
KSEF_BATCH_AUTO_CREATE_SUPPLIERS_SETTING_Help=When enabled, suppliers that cannot be matched to an existing third party will be automatically created during batch import. Matching is done by NIP (Polish tax ID) or EU VAT number. New suppliers are created with the name, address, and tax identifiers from the KSeF invoice. This setting is the default for batch imports and is remembered from the last batch import.
KSEF_BATCH_AUTO_CREATE_PRODUCTS_SETTING=Auto-create products during batch import
KSEF_BATCH_AUTO_CREATE_PRODUCTS_SETTING_Help=When enabled, products that cannot be matched to an existing product will be automatically created during batch import. Matching is attempted by product ref, supplier ref, and barcode/GTIN. New products are created with the description, ref, price, VAT rate, and barcode from the invoice line. If you do not need to track products or link invoice lines to your product catalog, you can leave this disabled - all unmatched lines will still be imported as free text descriptions. This setting is the default for batch imports and is remembered from the last batch import.
KSEF_PRODUCT_REF_USE_INDEKS_SETTING=Use supplier's product code (indeks) as product ref when auto-creating
KSEF_PRODUCT_REF_USE_INDEKS_SETTING_Help=When enabled, the supplier's product index code from the invoice line is used as the product reference when auto-creating new products. When disabled, Dolibarr's automatic numbering sequence is used instead.
KSEF_CUSTOMIZATION_CONFIG=Customization
KSEF_CUSTOMER_EXCLUSIONS=Customer Exclusions
