# Quick Start Section
KSEF_HowToUse=How to Use
KSEF_HowToUsePage=Usage Guide
KSEF_QuickStartGuide=Quick Start Guide
KSEF_GetCredentials=Get Your Credentials
KSEF_GetCredentialsDesc=You need either an authorization token or a qualified certificate from the KSeF portal. Certificates are preferred - tokens are being phased out at the end of 2026, and you'll need a certificate anyway if you want offline invoice capability.
KSEF_Portals=KSeF Portals
KSEF_CurrentEnvironment=current
KSEF_Important=Important
KSEF_PermissionsWarning=After generating your token or registering your certificate, make sure you configure the proper permissions in the KSeF portal under "Uprawnienia". Having valid credentials isn't enough - you need upload/download permissions assigned to them. This is a common oversight that results in authentication errors.

KSEF_ConfigureModule=Configure Module
KSEF_ConfigureModuleDesc=NIP is on the General tab. Tokens and certificates are on the Authentication tab, stored per environment so you don't re-enter them when switching.
KSEF_DefaultEnvironmentNote=The module defaults to Demo environment to prevent accidentally submitting official invoices while testing. Switch to Production (and upload the production certificates) once you're confident everything works correctly.
KSEF_ModuleSetup=Module Setup
KSEF_GoToSetup=Go to Setup

KSEF_TestConnection=Test Connection
KSEF_TestConnectionDesc=Use the test buttons to verify your connection and authentication work before attempting to submit invoices.
KSEF_TestNow=Test Now

KSEF_SubmitFirstInvoice=Submit Your First Invoice
KSEF_SubmitFirstInvoiceDesc=Open any validated invoice and click the KSeF button. If it comes back as ACCEPTED with a KSeF number, you're good to go. You can view the uploaded XML, the UPO, and generate either a Dolibarr PDF or a KSeF-app style PDF as needed.

# Configuration Section
KSEF_ConfigurationSection=Configuration
KSEF_Environments=Environments
KSEF_ENV_TEST_FullDesc=Submit fake invoices to fake companies with fake company information (e.g. company with NIP 9999999999) with non-secure certificate or token generated from publicly accessible test portal, just for testing the system out.
KSEF_ENV_DEMO_FullDesc=Submit fake invoices to fake companies with real company information and your Demo certificate or token, for testing system and verifying functionality. Invoices here are not legally binding.
KSEF_ENV_PRODUCTION_FullDesc=Submit real invoices with real company information and your Production certificate or token. These are legally binding invoices.

KSEF_Authentication=Authentication
KSEF_AuthenticationDesc=Certificates are the better choice, however tokens work fine for now but lose validity at the end of 2026. Offline invoicing requires an offline certificate regardless.

KSEF_HowTo_Config_PerEnvAuth=Per-Environment Credentials
KSEF_HowTo_Config_PerEnvAuthDesc=Each environment (TEST/DEMO/PRODUCTION) stores its own token and certificate. Switching environments automatically uses that environment's saved credentials. Configure each on the Authentication tab.

KSEF_HowTo_Config_PaymentDefaults=Default Payment Settings
KSEF_HowTo_Config_PaymentDefaultsDesc=Set default payment terms, method, and bank account on the Outgoing Invoices tab. These pre-fill when creating invoices if the customer has no specific settings configured. Customer-level values and linked source documents (orders/proposals) take priority.

KSEF_OptionalFields=Optional Fields
KSEF_OptionalFieldsDesc=The Outgoing Invoices tab has toggles for optional FA(3) fields like customer codes, product references, GTINs, and units of measure. Enable these if you have the data in Dolibarr and want it included in your KSeF submissions.

KSEF_HowTo_Config_Notes=Invoice Notes and Custom Fields
KSEF_HowTo_Config_NotesIntro=Include extra content in the KSeF XML from the invoice's public note and from invoice custom fields. Configure both on the Outgoing Invoices tab under "Invoice Notes and Custom Fields".
KSEF_HowTo_Config_NotesModes=The public note mode controls where and how the note is included in the KSeF XML. <b>Simple - Stopka</b> (default) sends the note as plain text in the invoice footer. <b>Simple - Dodatkowy Opis</b> sends it as a key-value entry with key "Uwagi", splitting into numbered entries if over 256 characters. <b>Key:Value - Dodatkowy Opis</b> parses each line at the first colon into a separate entry. Lines without a colon are skipped. Example:
KSEF_HowTo_Config_NotesKeyValueExample1=Order number: ZAM/2026/001
KSEF_HowTo_Config_NotesKeyValueExample2=Special instructions: Handle with care
KSEF_HowTo_Config_CustomFields=Custom fields from five entity types can be included: <b>Invoice</b> (applies to entire invoice), <b>Invoice Line</b> (linked to line via NrWiersza), <b>Product</b> (sourced from linked product per line, with NrWiersza), <b>Third Party</b> (sourced from customer), and <b>Project</b> (sourced from linked project). Create a new field with the form at the bottom of the section, or enable existing extrafields using the checkboxes.
KSEF_HowTo_Config_CustomFieldsTarget=For Invoice, Third Party, and Project extrafields, you can choose whether each field goes to <b>DodatkowyOpis</b> (key-value pairs in the XML) or <b>StopkaFaktury</b> (appended as "Label: Value" text in the invoice footer). Invoice Line and Product fields always go to DodatkowyOpis since they require line number linking (NrWiersza).
KSEF_HowTo_Config_Limits=Keys and values are capped at 256 characters. Simple mode splits longer notes into numbered entries. Key:Value and custom field values beyond 256 characters are truncated. StopkaFaktury text is capped at 3500 characters per entry.
KSEF_HowTo_Sending_Notes=Invoice Notes and Custom Fields
KSEF_HowTo_Sending_NotesEditing=Notes are edited on the invoice's Notes tab. A helper box below the textarea shows the current mode, a per-entry character breakdown, and any custom fields that will be included.
KSEF_HowTo_Sending_NotesPreview=The Notes tab and invoice card both show a preview panel listing exactly what will be sent, grouped by source. The panel reflects the last saved state.
KSEF_HowTo_Sending_NotesOverride=On the Notes tab, the "Notes mode (this invoice)" dropdown overrides the global setting for one invoice. Each option controls both where the note goes and how it's formatted. Configured custom fields are still included. Disabled suppresses everything for that invoice - notes and custom fields are omitted from both StopkaFaktury and DodatkowyOpis (boilerplate and registry numbers are not affected).

KSEF_HowTo_Sending_PDFPreview=PDF Preview
KSEF_HowTo_Sending_PDFPreviewDesc=A KSeF-style PDF preview is available on draft and validated invoices before submission. Use it to verify how the invoice will appear in KSeF format without submitting.

KSEF_HowTo_Config_OrderContract=Order and Contract Numbers
KSEF_HowTo_Config_OrderContractDesc=<b>NrZamowienia</b> (order/PO number) can be sourced from: Customer Reference (ref_client, default), linked sales order number, or an invoice extrafield. Multiple linked orders on one invoice result in multiple NrZamowienia entries. <b>NrUmowy</b> (contract number) can come from a third party extrafield (auto-populates from customer record) or an invoice extrafield (manual per invoice). Configure both on the Outgoing Invoices tab.

KSEF_HowTo_Config_Boilerplate=Footer Boilerplate
KSEF_HowTo_Config_BoilerplateDesc=A static text block on the Outgoing Invoices tab that appears in every invoice's StopkaFaktury. Use it for KRS registration, legal disclaimers, or GDPR clauses. Maximum 3500 characters. Not affected by per-invoice note overrides.

KSEF_CompanyIdentifiers=Company Identifiers
KSEF_CompanyIdentifiersDesc=NIP is required. KRS, REGON, and BDO are optional and will auto-populate from your company settings if configured there.
