KSEF_ValidateAndUpload_Desc=On draft invoices, handles validation and upload in one step. Can be hidden in settings if you prefer the payment-first workflow below
KSEF_UploadToKSEF_Desc=On validated, paid, or closed invoices, uploads to KSeF

KSEF_HowTo_Sending_PaymentFirst=Payment-First Workflow
KSEF_HowTo_Sending_PaymentFirstDesc=If you want payment data included in the KSeF XML: validate the invoice first, record payment(s), then click Upload to KSeF. The XML will include payment status, date, and amount. To encourage this flow, disable the "Validate and Upload" button on the Outgoing Invoices settings tab - this removes the one-click shortcut so the separate steps are more obvious.

KSEF_Statuses=Statuses
KSEF_STATUS_ACCEPTED_Desc=Invoice received a KSeF number, you're done
KSEF_STATUS_PENDING_Desc=Still processing, check back shortly
KSEF_STATUS_REJECTED_Desc=Check the error details and retry
KSEF_STATUS_OFFLINE_Desc=KSeF was unavailable, invoice saved locally with a deadline to submit online later

KSEF_ForeignCurrencyInvoices=Foreign Currency Invoices
KSEF_ForeignCurrencyDesc=For invoices in EUR or other non-PLN currencies, you need to fetch the NBP exchange rate before submitting and must have the multicurrency module enabled. When this is true, there is a button on the invoice card that pulls the rate from the last working day before the invoice date. Submission is blocked until the NBP exchange rate is pulled. You can choose whether to change the PLN price or the foreign currency price when exchange rate differs from the previous in settings, similar to multicurrency.

KSEF_BankAccountOnInvoice=Bank Account on Invoices
KSEF_BankAccountOnInvoiceDesc=If you send invoices with bank transfer as the payment method and want your bank account details (IBAN) to appear on the invoice, you need to assign a bank account to the invoice. Dolibarr can auto-fill this for you.
KSEF_BankAccount_Step1=Go to Bank/Cash and make sure your bank account has the IBAN filled in (SWIFT/BIC and bank name are optional but recommended)
KSEF_BankAccount_Step2=Go to the customer's Third Party card and set a default bank account - this will auto-fill on new invoices for that customer
KSEF_BankAccount_Step3=When creating an invoice with wire transfer payment, verify the Bank Account dropdown shows the correct account
KSEF_BankAccount_Step4=If the bank account is set and payment method is wire transfer, the IBAN will be included in the KSeF XML automatically

KSEF_AfterAcceptance=After Acceptance
KSEF_AfterAcceptanceDesc=Once accepted, you can generate a KSeF-style PDF visualization from the invoice card. If you have QR codes enabled in settings, the KSeF number also gets added to your regular invoice PDFs.

KSEF_CheckingStatusDesc=The KSeF tab on any invoice card shows all submission attempts for that invoice. The global Status page shows submissions across all invoices and highlights common errors:

# PDF Generation
KSEF_GenerateKSeFPDF=Generate KSeF-style PDF
KSEF_PDFRequiresSubmission=Invoice must be submitted to KSeF first
KSEF_PDFRequiresAccepted=Invoice must have ACCEPTED status in KSeF
KSEF_PDFRequiresOnline=Invoice must be submitted online (not offline mode)
