# Receiving Invoices Section
KSEF_ReceivingInvoices=Receiving Invoices
KSEF_ReceivingInvoicesDesc=Invoices that suppliers send you via KSeF can be synced into Dolibarr.
KSEF_Receiving_Step1=Go to the Incoming Invoices page:
KSEF_Receiving_Step2=Click "Sync from KSeF"
KSEF_Receiving_Step3=New invoices appear in the list
KSEF_ReceivingActions=For each invoice you can view the full details, download the original XML, download a PDF visualization, or verify it directly on the KSeF portal.

KSEF_ImportingToDolibarr=Importing to Dolibarr
KSEF_ImportingToDolibarrDesc=Incoming invoices can be imported as supplier invoices in Dolibarr. The module automatically matches suppliers by their tax identification numbers (NIP, EU VAT, or other professional identifiers configured in Dolibarr) and line items by product reference, supplier product reference, or barcode (GTIN).
KSEF_Importing_HowItWorks=How it works
KSEF_Importing_Step1=Sync incoming invoices from KSeF (manually or via scheduled job)
KSEF_Importing_Step2=Import invoices individually from the invoice's "Import to Dolibarr" tab, or use batch import from the incoming invoices list
KSEF_Importing_Step3=The module auto-matches the supplier and attempts to match each line item to an existing product - first by product reference, then by supplier reference, then by barcode
KSEF_Importing_Step4=Lines without a product match are imported as free text on the supplier invoice. If "Auto-create products when no match found" is enabled in module settings, new products are created instead
KSEF_Importing_Individual=Individual import
KSEF_Importing_IndividualDesc=Individual import allows you to review each invoice before importing. You can select or create a supplier (pre-filled from the invoice data) and choose which product to associate with each line item. A "+" button next to each line allows you to create a new product pre-filled with the reference, description, price, VAT rate, and barcode from the invoice.
KSEF_Importing_Batch=Batch import
KSEF_Importing_BatchDesc=Batch import processes multiple invoices at once from the incoming invoices list. It auto-matches suppliers and products where possible.
KSEF_Importing_StockNote=Importing an invoice does not automatically affect stock levels. Stock movements only occur when the imported supplier invoice is validated, and only if "Increase real stocks on validation of vendor invoice/credit note" is enabled in the Stock module settings:
KSEF_Importing_StockNoteLink=Stock module settings
KSEF_Importing_StockNoteFreeText=Lines imported as free text (without a linked product) will not affect stock regardless of this setting.

# Customer Exclusions Section
KSEF_CustomerExclusions=Customer Exclusions
KSEF_CustomerExclusionsDesc=Some customers don't need invoices sent to KSeF. You can exclude specific customers either from the module settings page or directly on the third party card using the exclusion checkbox.

# Troubleshooting Section
KSEF_Troubleshooting=Troubleshooting
KSEF_FindingErrorDetails=Finding Error Details
KSEF_FindingErrorDetailsDesc=Open the invoice, go to the KSeF tab, and view the error code and message. The global Status page also shows common errors across all submissions from the past 30 days:
KSEF_ViewingErrorDetails=Viewing Error Details
KSEF_ErrorDetailsLocation=To see detailed error information
KSEF_ClickInfoIcon=Click the info icon
KSEF_ScrollToKSEFSection=Scroll to KSeF section
KSEF_ConfigureNow=Configure now

KSEF_CommonIssues=Common Issues

KSEF_Issue_DuplicateNumber=Duplicate invoice number (Error 440)
KSEF_Issue_DuplicateNumber_Desc=This invoice number was already used in KSeF. Common in test/demo environments since data persists between sessions. Change the invoice number and retry.

KSEF_Issue_AuthFailed_Desc=First, verify your token or certificate hasn't expired. If credentials are valid, the most common cause is missing permissions in the KSeF portal. Go to "Moje uprawnienia" in the KSeF application and verify you have upload/download permissions configured. Valid authentication alone isn't sufficient - permissions must be explicitly assigned.

KSEF_Issue_NBPMissing=NBP rate missing
KSEF_Issue_NBPMissing_Desc=Foreign currency invoice without an exchange rate. Use the fetch button on the invoice card to pull the rate from NBP.

KSEF_Issue_Timeout_Desc=KSeF didn't respond in time. The submission might still be processing on their end. Check the status or retry.

KSEF_RetryLimits=Retry Limits
KSEF_RetryLimitsDesc=Failed submissions can be retried up to 30 times before being marked as permanently failed. Each attempt is logged in the submission history.


