KSEF_CountryRequirement=Third Party Country
KSEF_CountryRequirementDesc=Each third party (customer/supplier) should have their country set correctly. The module uses the country to determine how to identify the buyer in the KSeF XML: Polish buyers use NIP, EU buyers use the EU VAT number, and non-EU buyers use their foreign tax ID. If no country is set, the module will attempt to infer it from the VAT ID prefix (e.g. "DE" from "DE123456789"), otherwise it defaults to Poland.
