KSEF_TranslationOverridesHowToDesc=By default, Dolibarr does not display all professional ID fields (idprof3-6) for Polish companies. This module can override the field labels so that NIP, KRS, REGON, and BDO appear correctly on the Third Party card. Go to the module setup page, scroll to "Translation Overrides", and click "Apply Translation Overrides" for your languages. This only needs to be done once (or again after changing field mappings).
KSEF_HowTo_Config_VatRates=VAT Rate Codes for KSeF
KSEF_HowTo_Config_VatRatesIntro=KSeF uses specific codes to distinguish different types of 0%% VAT (exempt, reverse charge, not subject, intra-EU delivery, export). The module automatically creates these entries in Dolibarr's VAT rate dictionary when first activated, but they are <b>disabled by default</b> to keep the invoice VAT dropdown clean. Enable only the codes your business needs in the module settings.
KSEF_HowTo_Config_VatRatesCodes_Intro=How to enable VAT rate codes:
KSEF_HowTo_Config_VatRatesCodes_Step1=Go to the KSeF module settings page
KSEF_HowTo_Config_VatRatesCodes_Step2=In the <b>Optional Fields</b> section, find the <b>KSeF VAT Rate Codes</b> table
KSEF_HowTo_Config_VatRatesCodes_Step3=Check the codes you need (e.g. ZW for exempt services, WDT for EU deliveries)
KSEF_HowTo_Config_VatRatesCodes_Step4=Click Save - the enabled codes will appear in the VAT rate dropdown when creating invoice lines
KSEF_HowTo_Config_VatRatesCodes_Outro=The standard 0%% rate (without a code) is always available and auto-detects domestic/WDT/export based on the buyer's country. Supported codes:
KSEF_HowTo_Config_VatRatesTable_ColCode=Code
KSEF_HowTo_Config_VatRatesTable_ColUse=Use for
KSEF_HowTo_Config_VatRatesTable_None=(none)
KSEF_HowTo_Config_VatRatesTable_NoneUse=Standard 0%% - always available. The module automatically selects the correct KSeF type (domestic, intra-EU delivery, or export) based on the buyer's country.
KSEF_HowTo_Config_VatRatesTable_ZWUse=VAT exempt (zwolniony) - medical/dental services (art. 43), educational, financial, small business (art. 113)
KSEF_HowTo_Config_VatRatesTable_RCUse=Reverse charge (art. 17 ust. 1 pkt 7/8)
KSEF_HowTo_Config_VatRatesTable_NPUse=Not subject - goods/services outside Poland's territory
KSEF_HowTo_Config_VatRatesTable_NP2Use=Not subject II - intra-EU services (art. 100 ust. 1 pkt 4)
KSEF_HowTo_Config_VatRatesTable_WDTUse=Intra-EU delivery of goods - use when auto-detection is not sufficient
KSEF_HowTo_Config_VatRatesTable_EXUse=Export of goods - use when auto-detection is not sufficient
KSEF_HowTo_Config_VatRatesSetup=<b>When creating invoice lines</b>, select the correct VAT rate from the dropdown. For example, a dental practice should use <b>0%% (ZW)</b> for exempt services, while a regular domestic sale uses the standard 23%%. If you need a code that is not listed above, you can add custom entries via <b>Home > Setup > Dictionaries > VAT Rates</b>.
KSEF_HowTo_Config_VatExemptSetup=VAT Exempt Invoices (ZW) - Additional Setup
KSEF_HowTo_Config_VatExemptIntro=When issuing VAT-exempt invoices (code ZW), KSeF requires a legal basis for the exemption. The module provides two ways to set this - a global default and a per-product override.
KSEF_HowTo_Config_VatExemptSteps_S1Title=Step 1: Set a global default (required)
KSEF_HowTo_Config_VatExemptSteps_S1_1=In the KSeF module settings, under <b>Optional Fields</b>, find <b>VAT Exemption Legal Basis</b>
KSEF_HowTo_Config_VatExemptSteps_S1_2=Select the basis type - <b>Polish law</b> is correct for most Polish exemptions
KSEF_HowTo_Config_VatExemptSteps_S1_3=Enter the legal reference, e.g. <b>art. 43 ust. 1 pkt 18 ustawy o VAT</b> (medical/dental services)
KSEF_HowTo_Config_VatExemptSteps_S1Outro=This is used for all ZW invoice lines unless overridden at the product level.
KSEF_HowTo_Config_VatExemptSteps_S2Title=Step 2: Per-product override (optional - for businesses with multiple exemption types)
KSEF_HowTo_Config_VatExemptSteps_S2_1=Create a product/service extrafield, e.g. go to <b>Home > Setup > Other Setup > Extrafields</b>, select the <b>Products/Services</b> tab, and create a new text field (e.g. "zwolnienie_podstawa")
KSEF_HowTo_Config_VatExemptSteps_S2_2=On each exempt product card, fill in the specific legal basis for that product
KSEF_HowTo_Config_VatExemptSteps_S2_3=In the KSeF module settings, set <b>Per-Product Exemption Basis</b> to point at your new extrafield
KSEF_HowTo_Config_VatExemptSteps_S2Outro=When an invoice contains ZW lines, the module checks each product for its own basis first. If found, the product-level values are used (multiple different bases are joined with commas). If no product-level basis is found, the global default is used.
