KSEF_HowTo_Corrections=Correction Invoices (Faktury Korygujące)
KSEF_HowTo_Corrections_Intro=Polish tax law uses one concept for all invoice corrections: <b>faktura korygująca</b>. Dolibarr has two invoice types that serve this purpose. Both are sent to KSeF as KOR corrections referencing the original invoice, which must be on KSeF first.
KSEF_HowTo_Corrections_WhenTitle=When to use which type
KSEF_HowTo_Corrections_CreditNote=<b>Credit note</b> (Dolibarr "avoir") creates a negative invoice. Use for reductions only: returns, quantity decreases, post-sale discounts.
KSEF_HowTo_Corrections_Replacement=<b>Correction invoice</b> (Dolibarr "replacement") replaces the original entirely. Use for any change: amounts, VAT rates, addresses, or lines. Paid invoices can also be corrected this way.
KSEF_HowTo_Corrections_CreateTitle=Creating a correction
KSEF_HowTo_Corrections_CreateButton=After an invoice is accepted on KSeF, a <b>Create correction</b> button appears on the invoice card. It opens the creation page with the correction type and source invoice pre-selected.
KSEF_HowTo_Corrections_CreateRadio=Corrections can also be created from the invoice creation page by selecting the correction invoice radio and choosing the source invoice.
KSEF_HowTo_Corrections_PaidInvoice=For paid invoices, a discount is automatically applied to settle the correction when validated. The original invoice is restored to Paid/Closed status (not canceled).
KSEF_HowTo_Corrections_DetailsTitle=Correction details
KSEF_HowTo_Corrections_Reason=<b>Correction Reason</b> (PrzyczynaKorekty) - free-text reason for the correction. Recommended by Polish tax law but not required by the KSeF schema. Choose from preset reasons or enter custom text. Always stored in Polish. A default can be set on the Outgoing Invoices tab.
KSEF_HowTo_Corrections_Type=<b>Correction Type</b> (TypKorekty) - when the correction takes effect: original invoice date, correction invoice date, or another date. Optional.
KSEF_HowTo_Corrections_KsefTitle=What gets sent to KSeF
KSEF_HowTo_Corrections_KsefXml=The KOR XML references the original by its KSeF number. Line method is configurable on the Outgoing Invoices tab:
KSEF_HowTo_Corrections_MethodDiff=<b>Differential</b> - only delta lines showing the change
KSEF_HowTo_Corrections_MethodStan=<b>Before/After</b> (StanPrzed, default) - original and corrected state for each line
KSEF_HowTo_Corrections_CreditNoteDiff=Credit notes always use the Differential method regardless of this setting.
KSEF_HowTo_Corrections_ChainTitle=Correction chains
KSEF_HowTo_Corrections_Chain=A correction invoice can itself be corrected (korekta korekty). Each correction in the chain references the previous one. You cannot unvalidate or delete an invoice that has been corrected.
KSEF_HowTo_Corrections_ConfigTitle=Configuration
KSEF_HowTo_Corrections_Config=Correction settings are on the <b>Outgoing Invoices</b> settings tab under <b>Correction Invoices</b>: default correction reason and correction line method (Differential / Before-After).


KSEF_HowTo_AdvancedFields=Advanced FA(3) Fields
KSEF_HowTo_AdvancedFields_Intro=Optional fields that add extra data to the FA(3) XML. All configured on the <b>Outgoing Invoices</b> tab.
KSEF_HowTo_EntityFields=Entity Fields (Podmiot)
KSEF_HowTo_EntityFields_IDNabywcy=<b>Buyer ID (IDNabywcy)</b> - stable buyer identifier used across corrections when buyer data changes. Source from customer code or a thirdparty extrafield. Optional.
KSEF_HowTo_EntityFields_EORI=<b>EORI Numbers (NrEORI)</b> - EU customs/trade identifier. Set seller EORI in settings. Buyer EORI sources from a thirdparty extrafield. Only relevant for EU customs operations.
KSEF_HowTo_LineFields=Line-Level Fields (FaWiersz)
KSEF_HowTo_LineFields_GTU=<b>GTU Markers</b> - goods/services classification (GTU_01 through GTU_13) per invoice line. Source from a product extrafield. Aids JPK_VAT alignment.
KSEF_HowTo_LineFields_Procedura=<b>Procedura Markers</b> - procedure codes per invoice line (WSTO_EE, IED, TT_D, MPP, etc.). Source from a product extrafield.
KSEF_HowTo_LineFields_UUID=<b>Line UUID (UU_ID)</b> - unique identifier per invoice line for reliable line matching in corrections. Warning: visible on the KSeF PDF visualization, which may confuse recipients.
KSEF_HowTo_InvoiceFlags=Invoice Flags
KSEF_HowTo_InvoiceFlags_FP=<b>FP Flag</b> - art. 109 ust. 3d (taxpayers who lost VAT exemption). Enable only if applicable.
KSEF_HowTo_InvoiceFlags_TP=<b>TP Flag</b> - related party transactions (art. 32 ust. 2 pkt 1). Source from a thirdparty or invoice extrafield. Aids JPK_VAT alignment.
